WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:04.830
[ Wand crackling ]

00:04.830 --> 00:07.210
All jewelry must be removed
by the arresting officer.

00:07.210 --> 00:08.250
Do I have your permission
to proceed?

00:09.540 --> 00:11.540
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

00:11.540 --> 00:17.210
♪♪

00:17.210 --> 00:19.540
[ Wand crackling ]

00:19.540 --> 00:24.000
♪♪

00:24.000 --> 00:26.000
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

00:26.000 --> 00:34.960
♪♪

00:34.960 --> 00:37.500
[ Wand crackling ]

00:40.960 --> 00:44.880
♪ Whoa, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh,
whoa, oh, oh ♪

00:44.880 --> 00:50.460
♪ I'm gonna win for you
like I know you want me to do ♪

00:53.500 --> 00:55.460
Wesley: Hey.

00:55.460 --> 00:57.040
Happy Half-Year Anniversary.

00:57.040 --> 00:59.580
[ Chuckles ]
That's not a thing.

00:59.580 --> 01:02.380
Well, maybe not for
cynical police officers,

01:02.380 --> 01:03.620
but for
tender-hearted lawyers,

01:03.620 --> 01:05.750
it's totally a thing.

01:05.750 --> 01:09.080
But, hey, if you don't want
to go to n/naka tonight, eh...

01:09.080 --> 01:10.830
You got a reservation?

01:10.830 --> 01:12.170
You need to make those
like six --

01:12.170 --> 01:13.420
Six months in advance.
I know.

01:13.420 --> 01:15.710
I love your confidence.
[ Inhales sharply ]

01:17.460 --> 01:19.080
Wait.

01:19.080 --> 01:21.330
We've only been dating
for five months.

01:21.330 --> 01:23.290
[ Chuckles nervously ]

01:23.290 --> 01:25.330
Yeah, well, technically,
but --

01:25.330 --> 01:27.620
Did you make that reservation
for someone else

01:27.620 --> 01:29.880
and hope I wouldn't remember
exactly when we hooked up?

01:33.000 --> 01:35.000
If I say yes,
are you gonna say no?

01:35.000 --> 01:37.170
Are you kidding?
I would kill to eat there.

01:37.170 --> 01:38.960
[ Chuckles ]
But I'm gonna require

01:38.960 --> 01:41.880
some serious
shower time...

01:41.880 --> 01:43.670
Oh.
...for you
to make amends.

01:46.290 --> 01:48.710
Deal. Yeah.

01:48.710 --> 01:50.170
Whoa. Okay.

01:50.170 --> 01:52.170
Rachel:
We've got a problem.

01:52.170 --> 01:55.880
I just got an invitation
to a wedding.

01:55.880 --> 01:57.330
Yeah.
I don't do weddings.

01:57.330 --> 01:58.920
I don't know
what that means,

01:58.920 --> 02:01.000
and I wasn't
inviting you.

02:01.000 --> 02:03.540
Um, Lucy got
the same invitation.

02:03.540 --> 02:06.380
The couple getting married
is her ex-boyfriend

02:06.380 --> 02:08.120
and her ex-best friend.
Let me guess.

02:08.120 --> 02:09.670
They hooked up while Lucy
was still dating him.

02:09.670 --> 02:10.960
Living with him.
Mm.

02:10.960 --> 02:13.080
She's obviously
devastated,

02:13.080 --> 02:15.380
so maybe take it easy
on her today.

02:15.380 --> 02:17.380
Look, Chen is my rookie,
not my friend.

02:17.380 --> 02:18.540
My job is to train her,

02:18.540 --> 02:20.540
not help her through
her messy social life.

02:22.170 --> 02:23.120
[ Sighs ]

02:26.250 --> 02:29.790
Fine.
I'll dial it down, like, 2%.

02:29.790 --> 02:31.000
That's my guy.

02:31.000 --> 02:34.380
♪♪

02:34.380 --> 02:36.620
It is hot as the surface
of the sun out there.

02:36.620 --> 02:38.250
Yep.
Gonna be like that all week.

02:38.250 --> 02:40.000
Good thing we're all
in short sleeves now.

02:40.000 --> 02:41.170
The uniforms
are still wool.

02:41.170 --> 02:43.000
Today's gonna be
a nightmare.

02:43.000 --> 02:44.420
I'm just saying --

02:44.420 --> 02:46.290
I don't get out of the car
for less than a felony

02:46.290 --> 02:47.790
when the needle
hits 100.

02:47.790 --> 02:49.880
Your commitment to protecting
and serving is admirable.

02:49.880 --> 02:52.460
As long as I can do it
in comfort.

02:52.460 --> 02:55.170
You know the front row's
for the rookies, right?

02:55.170 --> 02:56.790
You hoping
I'll sit by you?

02:56.790 --> 02:58.080
I'm just telling you
how it is.

02:58.080 --> 02:59.330
The day
I need that from you

02:59.330 --> 03:00.250
is the day
I hang up my spurs.

03:01.710 --> 03:03.000
You know you're losing,
right?

03:03.000 --> 03:05.040
Sgt. Grey: Good morning.

03:05.040 --> 03:06.080
We've got ourselves a heat wave,

03:06.080 --> 03:07.420
which means what,
Officer West?

03:07.420 --> 03:09.170
Studies show
that a 1% loss of body mass

03:09.170 --> 03:10.460
due to sweating

03:10.460 --> 03:11.960
decreases
cognitive ability

03:11.960 --> 03:13.620
and increases
anxiety levels.

03:13.620 --> 03:15.330
Translation --
tempers will be short,

03:15.330 --> 03:16.960
drug and alcohol use up,

03:16.960 --> 03:18.710
so stay hydrated
and stay sharp.

03:18.710 --> 03:21.500
Now, while the rest of you
are baking in the sun,

03:21.500 --> 03:23.500
Officer Nolan
will be flop-sweating

03:23.500 --> 03:25.790
in his very first
preliminary court hearing.

03:25.790 --> 03:27.210
[ Laughter ]

03:27.210 --> 03:28.960
Oh, no flop sweats here,
sir.

03:28.960 --> 03:31.330
I have reviewed
the arrest report repeatedly.

03:31.330 --> 03:34.080
I am 100% ready to testify
on all the facts.

03:34.080 --> 03:35.710
Hmm. Bradford?

03:35.710 --> 03:37.250
When did you graduate
the Academy?

03:37.250 --> 03:39.880
Oh, that was September...
Exact date, Boot.

03:39.880 --> 03:41.880
What's your weapon's
serial number?

03:41.880 --> 03:43.880
I don't know the --
You need to know
the number by heart.

03:43.880 --> 03:45.960
For a DUI arrest?
I didn't even draw my weapon.

03:45.960 --> 03:48.380
If you don't even have
your personal information
squared away,

03:48.380 --> 03:50.540
how could you possibly know
the facts of the case?

03:50.540 --> 03:52.330
A defense attorney's job
is to screw you up on the stand

03:52.330 --> 03:54.250
by any means necessary.

03:54.250 --> 03:56.250
Sgt. Grey: Which means
everything that connects

03:56.250 --> 03:58.290
to your experience on the job
is in bounds.

03:58.290 --> 03:59.620
Got it?

03:59.620 --> 04:01.330
Yes, sir.

04:05.750 --> 04:07.290
You're driving today,
Boot.
What?

04:07.290 --> 04:08.920
You heard me.
Why?

04:08.920 --> 04:11.420
Look,
if you don't want to --
N-No, no. I do.

04:15.670 --> 04:17.290
[ Car door opens ]

04:20.880 --> 04:22.420
What's the catch?
Why does there
have to be a catch?

04:22.420 --> 04:24.620
There's always a catch.
Not today.

04:28.790 --> 04:30.040
[ Engine starts ]

04:31.750 --> 04:33.620
[ Horns honking ]

04:33.620 --> 04:35.120
Jackson:
Well, that can't be legal.

04:35.120 --> 04:36.960
It's not.
Light him up.

04:36.960 --> 04:39.040
[ Siren chirps ]

04:46.830 --> 04:48.290
You're not coming?

04:48.290 --> 04:50.210
It's a low-risk misdemeanor.
You got this.

04:53.380 --> 04:54.330
[ Car door closes ]

04:55.710 --> 04:57.960
[ Air conditioner turns on ]
Ahh.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.120
[ Indistinct conversations ]

05:06.960 --> 05:08.500
[ Sighs ]

05:13.080 --> 05:14.500
Hey.
Hi.

05:14.500 --> 05:16.040
What are you doing here?

05:16.040 --> 05:17.420
Well, it's your first time
in court.

05:17.420 --> 05:18.670
I thought you'd --
you'd appreciate

05:18.670 --> 05:19.830
a friendly face
in the gallery.

05:19.830 --> 05:21.380
Well, thank God.

05:21.380 --> 05:23.290
At roll call this morning,
Grey had me freaked out.

05:23.290 --> 05:25.500
He told me this was
predetermined to be a disaster.

05:25.500 --> 05:26.580
The first one always is.

05:26.580 --> 05:27.960
Was yours?

05:27.960 --> 05:29.620
Ugh. Especially mine.

05:29.620 --> 05:30.960
Good morning.

05:30.960 --> 05:32.830
Wesley. Whoa.

05:32.830 --> 05:35.120
You got a case
on the docket today?
Yep. Yours.

05:35.120 --> 05:37.620
Defense counsel ate
some bad lamb last night,

05:37.620 --> 05:39.790
asked me to step in.
Outstanding.

05:39.790 --> 05:41.000
N-Not about the --
the lamb,

05:41.000 --> 05:42.420
but that -- that it's --
that it's you.

05:42.420 --> 05:43.880
He's a little nervous.

05:43.880 --> 05:45.670
It's his first time
in court.

05:45.670 --> 05:47.750
Yeah. I get it.
My first time was disastrous.

05:47.750 --> 05:50.790
Look, I'll try to make it
as painless as possible, okay?

05:50.790 --> 05:52.040
Thank you very much.

05:52.040 --> 05:53.670
Hey, just remember --

05:53.670 --> 05:56.330
whatever happens,
it's not personal.

05:56.330 --> 05:58.290
Right.

05:58.290 --> 06:00.080
What does that mean?

06:00.080 --> 06:02.420
That I'm the only
friendly face here.

06:08.540 --> 06:10.750
[ Door opens ]

06:10.750 --> 06:13.380
[ Chains rattling ]

06:13.380 --> 06:15.880
That's my guy,
the one with the ponytail,

06:15.880 --> 06:18.750
Brant Reggie, 23-152,
DUI Drugs.

06:18.750 --> 06:22.170
[ Door closes ]

06:22.170 --> 06:24.380
How do I know
the guy next to him?

06:24.380 --> 06:28.710
Oh, that's, um,
Oscar Hutchinson.

06:28.710 --> 06:32.120
He was one of the prison bus
escapees we tracked down.

06:32.120 --> 06:34.460
He's kind of the reason
we're together.

06:34.460 --> 06:36.380
[ Door opens ]
How romantic.

06:36.380 --> 06:37.710
[ Door closes ]
Judge Stevens: Good morning.

06:37.710 --> 06:39.290
We've got a lot of cases
to get through today,

06:39.290 --> 06:40.540
so let's just jump right in.
[ Clears throat ]

06:40.540 --> 06:42.500
Uh, hi. Uh...

06:42.500 --> 06:44.210
Mr. Hutchinson, you've been
in my courtroom enough

06:44.210 --> 06:45.710
to know that
this isn't a Q&A.

06:45.710 --> 06:47.040
Yes, Your Honor.

06:47.040 --> 06:49.290
I just wanted to say
I don't mind going last.

06:49.290 --> 06:50.880
I think
these men beside me

06:50.880 --> 06:52.540
deserve to be heard from
first.

06:52.540 --> 06:54.210
And you're in no hurry
to go back in the hole.

06:54.210 --> 06:55.920
Interrupt me again,
and I'll have you gagged.

06:55.920 --> 06:57.500
Call the first case.

06:57.500 --> 06:58.830
Bailiff: People of
the State of California

06:58.830 --> 07:00.170
versus Jonathan Ryland,

07:00.170 --> 07:02.210
homicide
in the first degree.

07:03.580 --> 07:10.420
♪♪

07:10.420 --> 07:17.000
♪♪

07:17.000 --> 07:20.420
[ Spectators murmuring ]

07:20.420 --> 07:22.540
Is everything okay?

07:22.540 --> 07:24.330
[ Sniffles ]
That man killed our son.

07:28.330 --> 07:29.880
I'm so sorry.

07:34.290 --> 07:36.080
Amari: Thank you, sir.
Color's all off, man.

07:36.080 --> 07:38.330
It's not even
the right color green.
What's up, Amari?

07:38.330 --> 07:39.540
Man, this fool took
a counterfeit $100

07:39.540 --> 07:40.620
without even checking it.

07:40.620 --> 07:42.250
♪ Black and yellow ♪

07:42.250 --> 07:43.420
♪ Black and yellow,
black and yellow ♪

07:43.420 --> 07:45.170
They misspelled it
"hunderd."

07:45.170 --> 07:46.460
Don't get me started.

07:46.460 --> 07:47.580
Tim: You got
a description for us?

07:47.580 --> 07:49.790
Oh, better.

07:49.790 --> 07:51.460
♪ I run from my past,
I guess that makes... ♪

07:51.460 --> 07:53.790
Come on. You took a $100 bill
from this clown?

07:53.790 --> 07:55.040
Lucy:
How long ago was he here?

07:55.040 --> 07:56.250
30 minutes or so.

07:56.250 --> 07:58.080
I was at couple's counseling.

07:58.080 --> 07:59.540
Everything alright
with you and Serena?

07:59.540 --> 08:02.040
You know how it is.
Baby's teething.

08:02.040 --> 08:04.540
We're not sleeping.
I'm working long hours.

08:04.540 --> 08:07.750
Yeah. Well, look,
hang in there, alright?

08:07.750 --> 08:09.330
Yeah.

08:09.330 --> 08:10.710
Look, we'll put a BOLO out,
cruise the neighborhood.

08:10.710 --> 08:13.000
Hopefully we spot him.
Thanks.

08:13.000 --> 08:14.290
Oh, hey,
I'm still out $100, though.

08:14.290 --> 08:18.250
Uh, unfortunately,
yes.

08:18.250 --> 08:21.460
♪♪

08:21.460 --> 08:23.290
[ Door chimes ]

08:23.290 --> 08:24.960
You should've gloved up when you
touched the counterfeit bill

08:24.960 --> 08:26.290
in case we needed
to pull prints.

08:26.290 --> 08:28.210
You're right.
Um, I spaced.

08:28.210 --> 08:29.830
I'm sorry.

08:29.830 --> 08:31.880
Wait.

08:31.880 --> 08:33.790
Why didn't you say anything
when we were inside?

08:33.790 --> 08:35.670
No reason.

08:35.670 --> 08:38.540
You always call me out
in front of people

08:38.540 --> 08:39.920
when I screw up.

08:39.920 --> 08:41.710
First you let me drive,
now this?

08:41.710 --> 08:44.170
Why are you
being nice to me today?
I'm not.

08:45.880 --> 08:46.960
Did Rachel talk to you?

08:48.710 --> 08:51.290
She did.
I told her not to.

08:51.290 --> 08:52.710
Well, if it makes you
feel any better,

08:52.710 --> 08:54.080
I didn't want her to,
either.

08:54.080 --> 08:55.120
Look,
this isn't a big deal.

08:55.120 --> 08:56.380
You know,
I -- I'm over him,

08:56.380 --> 08:57.830
and I'm --
I'm happy for them.

08:57.830 --> 09:00.710
So I don't need any special
treatment from you, okay?

09:00.710 --> 09:02.290
Okay.

09:02.290 --> 09:03.540
Then I'm driving.

09:03.540 --> 09:05.290
What? But...

09:06.500 --> 09:07.290
[ Car door closes ]

09:11.880 --> 09:13.750
Hey. You called 911?

09:13.750 --> 09:15.000
Yeah.
I was hooking up the car,

09:15.000 --> 09:16.460
and I caught a whiff
of something really bad

09:16.460 --> 09:17.420
coming from that warehouse.

09:17.420 --> 09:19.290
Alright.
I'll check it out. Thanks.

09:22.380 --> 09:24.790
Whew. God.

09:24.790 --> 09:26.580
[ Sniffs ]

09:26.580 --> 09:27.710
[ Flashlight clicks ]

09:27.710 --> 09:28.920
[ Radio static crackles ]

09:28.920 --> 09:31.170
7-L-14,
possible DB at location.

09:31.170 --> 09:33.000
Stand by for confirmation.

09:33.000 --> 09:33.790
[ Radio static crackles ]

09:33.790 --> 09:42.000
♪♪

09:42.000 --> 09:43.120
[ Cellphone ringing ]

09:43.120 --> 09:45.210
[ Sighs ]

09:46.000 --> 09:47.540
[ Exhales heavily ]

09:47.540 --> 09:49.920
Hey.
Can I call you right back?

09:49.920 --> 09:51.830
What?

09:51.830 --> 09:53.420
You said visitation
was set.

09:53.420 --> 09:55.540
I changed my schedule.

09:55.540 --> 09:57.500
I haven't seen my daughter
in over a week.

09:57.500 --> 09:59.500
Look,
I don't want to play nice.

09:59.500 --> 10:00.540
I want my kid.

10:00.540 --> 10:01.710
[ Rattling ]

10:01.710 --> 10:03.120
♪♪

10:03.120 --> 10:04.830
I got to call you right back.

10:04.830 --> 10:06.000
[ Cellphone beeps ]

10:06.000 --> 10:10.540
♪♪

10:10.540 --> 10:15.380
♪♪

10:15.380 --> 10:17.830
[ Squishing ]

10:20.000 --> 10:22.790
[ Exhales sharply ]

10:22.790 --> 10:24.380
[ Crunching, squishing ]

10:24.380 --> 10:25.670
♪♪

10:25.670 --> 10:31.170
[ Dog snarling ]

10:31.170 --> 10:34.750
♪♪

10:34.750 --> 10:37.120
[ Dog barking ]

10:37.120 --> 10:46.880
♪♪

10:46.880 --> 10:47.920
[ Exhales sharply ]

10:47.920 --> 10:50.250
7-L-14, DB on scene.

10:50.250 --> 10:52.380
I need homicide
and forensic team.

10:52.380 --> 10:54.670
But first,
I need animal control.

10:54.670 --> 10:56.580
[ Radio beeps ]

10:56.580 --> 10:58.830
Officer Nolan, did you have
training at the Academy

10:58.830 --> 11:00.580
for DUI suspects?
Uh, yes, sir.

11:00.580 --> 11:03.250
40 hours of alcohol
intoxication recognition.

11:03.250 --> 11:04.670
Did they test you
on that training?

11:04.670 --> 11:05.710
Of course.

11:05.710 --> 11:08.000
And did you score 100%?

11:09.380 --> 11:10.830
No, but I --

11:10.830 --> 11:13.040
Okay, so, on the date
in question --

11:13.040 --> 11:14.380
March 16th.
Yes. That date.

11:14.380 --> 11:16.460
Did you see my client
behind the wheel?

11:16.460 --> 11:18.580
N-No. Your client was
already out of the car

11:18.580 --> 11:20.170
by the time
we arrived on scene,

11:20.170 --> 11:22.670
but the driver of
the vehicle he hit --
Allegedly hit.

11:22.670 --> 11:24.620
And please only answer
the questions that I ask you.

11:24.620 --> 11:26.670
Now, did you get fingerprints
from the steering wheel

11:26.670 --> 11:29.420
to prove that my client
was the driver?

11:29.420 --> 11:31.920
No,
but the other driver --

11:31.920 --> 11:33.210
The other driver,
as you call him,

11:33.210 --> 11:34.540
suffered a head injury.

11:34.540 --> 11:36.210
Are you telling me
that you identified my client

11:36.210 --> 11:38.790
based solely on
that man's say-so?

11:40.960 --> 11:43.290
Man: [ Clears throat ]

11:43.290 --> 11:45.500
Your client owns the car.

11:45.500 --> 11:47.250
Your Honor, can you please
instruct the witness

11:47.250 --> 11:48.290
to answer my question?

11:48.290 --> 11:50.540
Officer.
Yeah. Uh, yes.

11:50.540 --> 11:54.000
I ID'd your client
as the driver of the vehicle

11:54.000 --> 11:56.460
based on
the witness statement.

11:56.460 --> 11:58.580
Okay.

11:58.580 --> 12:03.920
♪♪

12:03.920 --> 12:05.540
[ Door buzzes ]

12:05.540 --> 12:07.460
Lopez: How could I have known
he wasn't wearing pants?

12:07.460 --> 12:09.460
No, not just pants --
bottoms of any kind.

12:09.460 --> 12:11.290
I'll never be able
to unsee that.

12:12.500 --> 12:14.710
Whoa!
My man, close it up.

12:14.710 --> 12:17.380
[ Laughs ]

12:17.380 --> 12:19.290
Lucy:
You think I'm being stupid,

12:19.290 --> 12:21.170
letting that invitation
bother me.

12:21.170 --> 12:22.580
You said
it wasn't bothering you,

12:22.580 --> 12:23.830
and I was relieved we didn't
have to talk about it.

12:23.830 --> 12:26.080
Why the hell would they
invite me to their wedding?

12:26.080 --> 12:27.670
To further humiliate me?

12:27.670 --> 12:29.620
[ Sighs ]

12:29.620 --> 12:31.750
Maybe they're trying
to make amends.
Amends.

12:31.750 --> 12:34.080
By making me
starve myself for a month

12:34.080 --> 12:35.750
so I can fit into
a drop-dead sexy dress and --

12:35.750 --> 12:37.710
Hey. Up ahead.

12:37.710 --> 12:38.670
That's the counterfeit guy.

12:38.670 --> 12:40.120
[ Police radio chatter ]

12:40.120 --> 12:41.880
[ Siren chirps ]

12:41.880 --> 12:44.580
Hey! Hands on the hood.
Let's go.

12:44.580 --> 12:45.880
[ Sighs ]

12:45.880 --> 12:47.920
Alright.
Spread your legs apart.

12:47.920 --> 12:51.750
[ Cellphone alarms blaring ]

12:51.750 --> 12:57.380
♪♪

12:57.380 --> 12:59.120
[ Dog barking ]

12:59.120 --> 13:02.500
[ Sighs,
cellphone alarm blaring ]

13:02.500 --> 13:06.620
♪♪

13:06.620 --> 13:08.790
[ Cellphone alarms blaring ]

13:10.830 --> 13:12.580
This can't be real.

13:12.580 --> 13:14.330
♪♪

13:14.330 --> 13:19.380
[ Cellphone alarms blaring ]

13:19.380 --> 13:20.960
[ Spectators murmuring,
shouting ]

13:20.960 --> 13:22.710
♪♪

13:22.710 --> 13:25.170
-It's the emergency...
-Look. You think this is real?

13:25.170 --> 13:27.330
[ Murmuring,
shouting continues ]

13:27.330 --> 13:31.460
♪♪

13:31.460 --> 13:33.210
What's happening?

13:33.210 --> 13:41.620
♪♪

13:41.620 --> 13:43.290
[ Murmuring,
shouting continues ]

13:49.750 --> 13:51.500
[ Tires squeal ]

13:51.500 --> 13:54.250
Man: Go! Go! Go! Come on!
We got to get out of here!

13:54.250 --> 13:55.670
[ Tires squeal ]

13:59.170 --> 14:01.830
[ Metal crunches,
horns honking ]

14:01.830 --> 14:03.290
What do we do?
Let him go.

14:03.290 --> 14:04.710
We got to get
back to the station.

14:04.710 --> 14:06.250
[ Tires squeal ]

14:06.250 --> 14:07.790
[ Car door closes ]

14:07.790 --> 14:10.120
[ Engine starts ]

14:10.120 --> 14:12.170
[ Tires squeal ]

14:13.500 --> 14:15.170
[ Indistinct conversations,
gavel banging ]

14:15.170 --> 14:18.080
Order! Order in my court!

14:18.080 --> 14:20.120
Order! Order!

14:20.120 --> 14:22.380
Everyone, be still!

14:22.380 --> 14:25.080
Clearly, we can't continue,
given the missile alert.

14:25.080 --> 14:26.960
Deputy, take the prisoners
back to holding.

14:26.960 --> 14:29.040
Let's go. Come on.
Screw that.
There's a nuke coming!

14:29.040 --> 14:30.620
[ Indistinct shouting ]

14:30.620 --> 14:32.170
Got anything?

14:32.170 --> 14:33.460
The -- The lines
are already jammed.

14:33.460 --> 14:34.750
[ Sighs ]
People are panicking.

14:34.750 --> 14:36.290
We got to help them out.
Should we evacuate?

14:36.290 --> 14:37.420
No. No. Um...

14:38.880 --> 14:41.330
Hey, hey, everybody.
Excuse me.

14:41.330 --> 14:43.540
Everyone, if I can have
your attention, please.

14:43.540 --> 14:46.420
Uh, I'm Jessica Russo,
Department of Homeland Security.

14:46.420 --> 14:48.670
Now, I haven't gotten
in touch with my office,

14:48.670 --> 14:51.830
but there is a good chance
that this is not real.

14:51.830 --> 14:53.120
That's right.
That's right.

14:53.120 --> 14:54.420
There was
a false missile alert

14:54.420 --> 14:55.830
out of Hawaii
just last year.

14:55.830 --> 14:57.750
[ Whispering
indistinctly ]
There's no need to panic.

14:57.750 --> 14:59.120
What if it's not fake?

14:59.120 --> 15:00.460
Well, then you got
about 28 minutes

15:00.460 --> 15:02.380
until you find out
what Hell feels like.

15:02.380 --> 15:04.540
Okay, that kind of talk
isn't helping anything.

15:04.540 --> 15:08.040
The DHS has scenarios
planned for this situation.

15:08.040 --> 15:09.830
We have.
Yes, we have.

15:09.830 --> 15:14.580
And, um, the most likely target
is downtown.

15:14.580 --> 15:16.120
[ Indistinct shouting ]

15:16.120 --> 15:17.170
Where we are.
Jessica: Okay. Wait!

15:17.170 --> 15:18.000
[ Gavel bangs ]
Judge Stevens: Order.

15:18.000 --> 15:19.620
Jessica: Wait! Wait!

15:19.620 --> 15:22.620
The blast radius is likely
between 10 to 15 miles.

15:22.620 --> 15:25.790
And with an impact expected
in 27 minutes,

15:25.790 --> 15:29.330
there isn't enough time
to get far enough away,

15:29.330 --> 15:31.920
which is why we need
to get underground.

15:31.920 --> 15:33.420
Judge, sir, i-is --

15:33.420 --> 15:34.750
is there a bomb shelter
in this building?

15:34.750 --> 15:39.170
No, but the holding cells
are downstairs.

15:39.170 --> 15:40.750
Let's go.
I hate to break it
to you,

15:40.750 --> 15:42.580
but those cells leak
when it rains.

15:42.580 --> 15:45.620
They're not gonna do squat
in a nuclear attack.

15:45.620 --> 15:46.750
Okay -- [ Sighs ]

15:46.750 --> 15:47.620
Deputy Nickerson:
Now. Come on. Let's go.

15:47.620 --> 15:50.120
[ All shouting indistinctly ]

15:52.790 --> 15:54.000
[ Dog barking ]

15:54.000 --> 15:56.420
[ Cellphone beeps ]

15:56.420 --> 15:58.920
[ Line ringing ]

15:58.920 --> 16:01.040
Come on. Come on.
Come on. Come on.

16:01.040 --> 16:02.830
[ Exhales heavily ]

16:02.830 --> 16:05.540
[ Line beeps ]

16:05.540 --> 16:07.540
[ Exhales sharply ]
Damn it.

16:07.540 --> 16:09.040
[ Breathes deeply ]

16:11.330 --> 16:13.000
Here goes nothing.

16:13.000 --> 16:14.170
♪♪

16:14.170 --> 16:15.380
[ Spray hissing ]

16:15.380 --> 16:17.040
[ Dog whimpers ]

16:17.960 --> 16:20.880
[ Dog barking ]

16:20.880 --> 16:22.330
♪♪

16:22.330 --> 16:28.040
[ Breathing deeply ]

16:28.040 --> 16:31.000
[ Horns honking,
sirens wailing ]

16:31.000 --> 16:32.790
Sgt. Grey: Listen up.

16:32.790 --> 16:35.920
LAPD has not been able
to verify the alert is real.

16:35.920 --> 16:37.420
However, real or not,

16:37.420 --> 16:39.420
everyone in the city
is panicking right now.

16:39.420 --> 16:41.880
So I don't care if you've been
off the street for 20 years.

16:41.880 --> 16:43.880
If you got a badge,
get out there.

16:43.880 --> 16:47.500
First priority --
to secure sensitive targets.

16:47.500 --> 16:49.080
Next, protect the community.

16:49.080 --> 16:50.710
Ignore petty crimes.

16:50.710 --> 16:52.330
Focus on people,
not property.

16:52.330 --> 16:55.420
Look, I know you're scared.
I'm scared, too.

16:55.420 --> 16:57.040
But people out there
are counting on us,

16:57.040 --> 16:58.580
and we will help them.

16:58.580 --> 16:59.880
Man: Yeah.

16:59.880 --> 17:01.120
Okay, let's get to work.

17:01.120 --> 17:07.790
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:09.960 --> 17:11.880
What can I do?
Stay here.

17:11.880 --> 17:12.920
If this is real,
there's a place to seek shelter

17:12.920 --> 17:14.250
in the parking garage.

17:14.250 --> 17:15.500
Stay with me.

17:15.500 --> 17:17.120
I can't.

17:17.120 --> 17:18.880
I'm the guy
that catches the nuke.

17:18.880 --> 17:21.120
It's actually
a pretty prestigious assignment.

17:21.120 --> 17:22.540
You're an idiot.

17:22.540 --> 17:23.920
Thanks.

17:29.380 --> 17:31.710
The world could be ending.

17:31.710 --> 17:34.380
I don't think anybody's gonna
begrudge you a little PDA.

17:34.380 --> 17:35.960
Come here.

17:39.080 --> 17:40.880
I'll see you later.
You better.

17:44.170 --> 17:46.620
Why is everyone
running around, Mommy?
We're having a drill,

17:46.620 --> 17:48.500
like we were having at school
when I picked you up.

17:48.500 --> 17:50.880
But then why does
everyone look so scared?

17:50.880 --> 17:52.880
Because
they're good actors, baby.

17:52.880 --> 17:54.670
Detective,
why aren't you on the street?

17:54.670 --> 17:56.540
'Cause I need to take care
of my daughter.

18:01.210 --> 18:03.170
Understood.

18:03.170 --> 18:04.750
Hi, there.

18:04.750 --> 18:06.250
I'm Sergeant Grey.

18:06.250 --> 18:08.330
Lila.
Nice to meet you, Lila.

18:08.330 --> 18:09.920
Do you mind if I talk
to your mom for a minute?

18:09.920 --> 18:11.710
Sure.

18:11.710 --> 18:14.580
Uh, go get a snack
from the machine, baby. Okay?

18:14.580 --> 18:16.210
Um, I can help her.

18:16.210 --> 18:17.830
Thank you.
Of course.

18:20.580 --> 18:22.120
Is it real?

18:22.120 --> 18:24.000
I don't know.

18:24.000 --> 18:25.540
Tell me --
how was the traffic coming in?

18:25.540 --> 18:26.880
Any chance for people
to get clear?

18:27.580 --> 18:29.750
No.

18:29.750 --> 18:33.000
♪♪

18:33.000 --> 18:35.790
[ Horns honking,
sirens wailing ]

18:35.790 --> 18:38.620
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

18:38.620 --> 18:43.620
[ Indistinct conversations ]

18:43.620 --> 18:44.620
Why don't you just
let us go, man?

18:44.620 --> 18:46.000
It's the end of the world.

18:46.000 --> 18:47.290
Give us a few minutes
of freedom.

18:47.290 --> 18:49.290
Don't make us die
in these chains.
Shut up, Oscar.

18:49.290 --> 18:51.250
You're not getting out
of those cuffs.
We ain't asking.

18:51.250 --> 18:53.960
Back up. Back up.
Right now. Right now.

18:53.960 --> 18:55.620
[ Chains rattling ]

18:55.620 --> 18:59.580
♪♪

18:59.580 --> 19:01.790
Hey, um,
I can't get ahold of Angela.

19:01.790 --> 19:03.330
Can I use your radio?
Yeah.

19:03.330 --> 19:04.880
[ Radio crackles ]

19:04.880 --> 19:06.500
7-Adam-07,
go to channel 15.

19:06.500 --> 19:08.040
Just turn the dial on top.
Thank you.

19:10.120 --> 19:11.710
Angela, it's me.

19:11.710 --> 19:14.670
Wesley?
Hey, how's it going?

19:14.670 --> 19:16.670
Oh, you know, pretty good
for the end of the world.

19:16.670 --> 19:18.710
I'm bummed we're gonna miss
our reservation.

19:18.710 --> 19:21.960
Look, we're not.
This is just a false alarm.

19:21.960 --> 19:23.120
Okay?
Yeah.

19:23.120 --> 19:24.710
Hey. You alright?

19:24.710 --> 19:25.880
There's a bomb shelter
at the public school

19:25.880 --> 19:27.330
two blocks west, alright?
Head there.

19:27.330 --> 19:28.710
Where are you?

19:28.710 --> 19:30.540
I'm at the courthouse
with Nolan

19:30.540 --> 19:31.880
and Jessica and a bunch
of scared people.

19:31.880 --> 19:33.170
Two blocks west.
Head there.

19:33.170 --> 19:34.330
Are you going down
to the bomb shelter?

19:36.460 --> 19:38.460
Judge Stevens
said there isn't one.

19:38.460 --> 19:41.710
Criminal courthouse
on Spring?
Yeah.

19:41.710 --> 19:43.250
There's definitely
a fallout shelter.

19:43.250 --> 19:44.620
I was down there once
as a rookie.

19:44.620 --> 19:46.920
♪♪

19:46.920 --> 19:48.500
Hey.

19:48.500 --> 19:50.500
Nolan.

19:50.500 --> 19:52.580
Angela says this place
does have a bomb shelter.

19:53.710 --> 19:55.250
Are you safe
where you are?

19:55.250 --> 19:57.880
[ Shouting,
honking continues ]

19:57.880 --> 20:00.080
Angela.
Are you still there?

20:00.080 --> 20:02.120
Yeah.
I'm heading underground.

20:04.080 --> 20:06.460
Okay. I love you.

20:06.460 --> 20:08.000
Love you, too.

20:08.000 --> 20:13.120
♪♪

20:13.120 --> 20:14.710
The judge is gone.

20:14.710 --> 20:16.920
So is the ADA, the --
the bailiff,

20:16.920 --> 20:18.620
and a bunch of other people
from the gallery.

20:18.620 --> 20:22.330
What's happening?

20:22.330 --> 20:24.540
The judge lied to us
about the bomb shelter.

20:24.540 --> 20:30.040
♪♪

20:30.040 --> 20:31.540
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Wait! Wait! Wait! Wait!

20:31.540 --> 20:32.880
Step back.
What are you doing?

20:32.880 --> 20:34.750
What I have to.

20:39.960 --> 20:42.830
-Back up. I'm closing this door.
-And what about the rest of us?

20:42.830 --> 20:45.170
If she's right about the nuke,
then this is ground zero.

20:45.170 --> 20:47.170
Won't be safe
to go outside for weeks.

20:47.170 --> 20:49.460
We don't have the supplies
in here for all of you.

20:49.460 --> 20:51.670
So you're gonna kill a cop
and all these others

20:51.670 --> 20:52.960
just to save yourselves?

20:52.960 --> 20:54.880
And the rest of you --
you're all good with that?!

20:54.880 --> 20:56.330
I'm not gonna
tell you again.

20:56.330 --> 20:58.500
Back up
so I can close this door.

20:58.500 --> 21:00.750
Okay. Okay, fine.
You win. I give up.

21:00.750 --> 21:02.960
[ People gasp ]

21:02.960 --> 21:04.380
Pretty cool, right?

21:04.380 --> 21:06.080
They taught me that
at the Academy.

21:07.500 --> 21:08.750
Come on.

21:08.750 --> 21:10.330
You're making
a big mistake.

21:10.330 --> 21:11.750
And you're under arrest.
Sit down right there.

21:11.750 --> 21:13.250
Get cozy.

21:13.250 --> 21:15.000
Here we go.
Come in.

21:15.000 --> 21:16.210
Hands.

21:18.210 --> 21:19.960
No, no, no! Not him!

21:19.960 --> 21:21.620
Hey. They're human beings
with rights.

21:21.620 --> 21:23.380
He killed our boy
in cold blood.

21:23.380 --> 21:26.040
Aw.
You better back up, mami,

21:26.040 --> 21:27.750
or you'll be next.
You --

21:27.750 --> 21:29.330
-Get off me!
-Okay. Alright. Alright.

21:29.330 --> 21:30.790
-Hey. Take it easy.
-Hey, hey, hey!

21:30.790 --> 21:32.330
Alright, we're not leaving
anyone outside, okay?

21:32.330 --> 21:34.540
So everyone back up.
Here we go. Come on.

21:34.540 --> 21:35.750
Jessica: Back up.
Let's get these prisoners
over to the back here.

21:35.750 --> 21:37.420
We can segregate them
on the benches.

21:37.420 --> 21:39.420
Here. Take that.

21:39.420 --> 21:42.580
Folks, in this way.
Keep moving.

21:42.580 --> 21:43.670
Go ahead
and sit down, sir.

21:45.290 --> 21:47.290
Nolan: Is that everyone?
Thank you.

21:47.290 --> 21:48.960
Alright.

21:48.960 --> 21:50.710
[ Grunts ]

21:50.710 --> 21:53.380
Be a lot more comfortable
without this chain, you know?

21:53.380 --> 21:55.790
We can keep the cuffs on.
Don't push your luck, Oscar.

21:55.790 --> 21:57.580
Ah, that's all
I know how to do.

21:57.580 --> 21:59.120
[ Door closes ]

21:59.120 --> 22:00.460
[ Lock engages ]

22:00.460 --> 22:02.920
♪♪

22:02.920 --> 22:05.670
[ Breathing heavily ]

22:05.670 --> 22:10.080
♪♪

22:18.040 --> 22:20.880
There's barely any air
moving in here at all.

22:20.880 --> 22:22.710
Well, the judge
was right about one thing.

22:22.710 --> 22:24.250
With this many people
in here,

22:24.250 --> 22:25.880
these supplies
won't even last a week.

22:25.880 --> 22:28.290
I'm surprised
we haven't gotten an update.

22:28.290 --> 22:29.750
Control, 7-Adam-15.
Come in.

22:32.460 --> 22:34.920
Control?

22:34.920 --> 22:37.500
No bars.
Alright.

22:37.500 --> 22:40.880
So, we know radio frequencies
and mobile signals

22:40.880 --> 22:42.210
are blocked by the shelter.

22:42.210 --> 22:44.170
Let's hope it does as well
against radiation.

22:50.540 --> 22:52.670
[ Clack ]

22:52.670 --> 22:54.880
This thing hasn't worked
since the Reagan administration.

22:57.750 --> 22:59.670
So, now all we can do
is wait.

22:59.670 --> 23:01.750
[ Sighs ]

23:01.750 --> 23:05.500
[ Sirens wailing ]

23:05.500 --> 23:07.040
13 minutes.

23:07.040 --> 23:08.330
Stop checking the time.

23:08.330 --> 23:09.880
Are you serious?

23:09.880 --> 23:11.420
We're about to be burned up
by a giant fireball.

23:11.420 --> 23:13.170
"A," no, we're not.
It's a false alarm.

23:13.170 --> 23:14.670
And, "B,"
counting down the minutes

23:14.670 --> 23:16.830
wouldn't accomplish anything,
even if it was real.

23:16.830 --> 23:19.120
So, what, you just want me
to think about something else?

23:19.120 --> 23:20.710
Pretty much.
Can't be done.

23:20.710 --> 23:22.000
Really?

23:23.540 --> 23:25.500
Okay.

23:25.500 --> 23:26.580
How would you sabotage
that wedding?

23:26.580 --> 23:28.420
What?

23:28.420 --> 23:29.920
Don't tell me you didn't
lie awake all night

23:29.920 --> 23:32.540
fantasizing about it.
I -- I didn't.

23:32.540 --> 23:35.540
Lying to me in your last moments
on Earth is a bad look.

23:35.540 --> 23:37.460
You said
it was a false alarm.

23:37.460 --> 23:39.080
Fine.

23:39.080 --> 23:41.420
I'd cancel
the rehearsal dinner,

23:41.420 --> 23:43.580
change the registry
to a bondage Web store,

23:43.580 --> 23:45.880
pay a gang of clowns
to storm their wedding,

23:45.880 --> 23:49.000
and hire a chopper to fly over
their outdoor reception,

23:49.000 --> 23:50.420
see how well
their wedding cake stands up

23:50.420 --> 23:52.790
to the rotor wash of
a Sikorsky helicopter.

23:52.790 --> 23:53.880
Didn't think about it,
huh?

23:53.880 --> 23:55.580
[ Sighs ]

23:55.580 --> 23:57.920
How is revenge what
we're focusing on right now?

23:57.920 --> 24:01.170
It's tangible, okay?
You can hold on to it.

24:01.170 --> 24:03.790
Imminent nuclear death
is totally unrelatable.

24:03.790 --> 24:05.330
Now, speaking of revenge,

24:05.330 --> 24:07.830
I have a friend at USC
who studies cockroaches.

24:07.830 --> 24:09.420
I'm sure he could
loan you a few hundred

24:09.420 --> 24:10.670
to release
at the wedding.

24:10.670 --> 24:11.830
[ Radio beeps, crackles ]

24:11.830 --> 24:14.540
[ Radio chatter ]

24:14.540 --> 24:17.830
[ Indistinct conversations,
telephone ringing ]

24:21.250 --> 24:24.080
Mommy,
what's really going on?

24:24.080 --> 24:25.790
I told you, honey.
It's a drill.

24:25.790 --> 24:28.670
Please don't lie.

24:28.670 --> 24:31.040
Daddy says that's why
we can't see you anymore.

24:31.040 --> 24:34.120
Don't you want
to tell the truth?

24:36.460 --> 24:38.790
Of course I do, honey.
I --

24:38.790 --> 24:41.380
I just --

24:41.380 --> 24:44.830
My previous job,
I had to lie a lot...

24:44.830 --> 24:46.920
to fool criminals, so...

24:46.920 --> 24:48.500
Why do you want
to fool me?

24:48.500 --> 24:49.960
Are you mad at me?

24:49.960 --> 24:51.210
Of course not.
No, honey.

24:51.210 --> 24:54.080
I, um -- I love you.

24:56.040 --> 24:57.460
I'll make you a deal.

24:57.460 --> 24:59.330
I'll stop sleeping
with a night light

24:59.330 --> 25:01.920
if you tell the truth,
okay?

25:01.920 --> 25:03.250
Okay.

25:03.250 --> 25:08.420
♪♪

25:08.420 --> 25:12.120
[ Breathes deeply ]

25:12.120 --> 25:13.920
[ Indistinct conversations ]

25:26.330 --> 25:28.580
[ Whispering
indistinctly ]

25:33.710 --> 25:35.750
And here I thought the most
stressful part of my day

25:35.750 --> 25:36.830
would be going to court.

25:36.830 --> 25:38.500
At least we're together.

25:38.500 --> 25:40.460
Yeah.

25:43.120 --> 25:44.880
Thank you for coming
to support me.

25:44.880 --> 25:46.330
You're welcome.

25:53.120 --> 25:55.540
Can I, um -- [ Chuckles ]

25:55.540 --> 25:57.170
Can I confess something?

25:57.170 --> 25:59.040
You were already here
for a meeting.

25:59.040 --> 26:00.330
You knew?

26:00.330 --> 26:01.710
Yeah,
but it didn't matter.

26:01.710 --> 26:08.670
♪♪

26:08.670 --> 26:10.380
[ Panting ]
10 minutes.

26:10.380 --> 26:11.920
We still have time to get
to the fallout shelter

26:11.920 --> 26:14.210
at the courthouse,
hook up with Wesley.

26:14.210 --> 26:16.790
[ Woman shouting indistinctly ]
Yeah, maybe we should,
just to be safe.

26:16.790 --> 26:19.120
All: All hail
Children of the Stars.

26:19.120 --> 26:21.880
Aurora: The worthy will
ascend into the heavens!

26:21.880 --> 26:24.460
All: All hail
Children of the Stars.
We are not going
to the shelter, are we?

26:24.460 --> 26:26.670
Aurora: We will wait for your
arrival, Noon Star Harvesters.

26:26.670 --> 26:27.670
All: All hail
Children of the Stars.

26:31.540 --> 26:34.210
Aurora: Today the saviors
will gather our souls.

26:34.210 --> 26:36.040
All: All hail
Children of the Stars.

26:36.040 --> 26:38.540
Aurora: The worthy
will ascend into the heavens.

26:38.540 --> 26:41.830
All: All hail
Children of the Stars.
Hey!

26:41.830 --> 26:43.540
Aurora:
We await your arrival...
How about you come down
from there?

26:43.540 --> 26:45.040
...Noon Star Harvesters.

26:45.040 --> 26:46.750
All: All hail
Children of the Stars.
No.

26:46.750 --> 26:48.380
It's almost our time,
but there's nothing to fear.

26:48.380 --> 26:49.750
This was all prophesized --

26:49.750 --> 26:50.920
"Like a clarion call,

26:50.920 --> 26:52.750
word shall spread
of Our Saviors From Above.

26:52.750 --> 26:54.330
Heed ye
the Noon Star Harvesters,

26:54.330 --> 26:56.170
for they shall descend
from the heavens

26:56.170 --> 26:57.620
so The Worthy
can ascend."

26:57.620 --> 27:00.120
So sayeth
The Prophet Jedediah.

27:00.120 --> 27:02.620
All: All hail
Children of the Stars.

27:02.620 --> 27:05.420
Okay. So, you're saying
the missile --
Isn't a missile.

27:05.420 --> 27:07.500
It is a cloak behind which
our saviors will come to us,

27:07.500 --> 27:09.880
and we will step out to meet
them at the appointed time,

27:09.880 --> 27:12.290
ascending into
their interstellar embrace.

27:12.290 --> 27:15.710
All: All hail
Children of the Stars.

27:17.000 --> 27:18.500
Today the Saviors will...

27:18.500 --> 27:20.710
So, they're clearly crazy.
Can we go now?

27:20.710 --> 27:23.120
All: All hail
Children of the Stars.
You can.

27:23.120 --> 27:25.620
But I'm not leaving until I get
them down off that ledge.

27:25.620 --> 27:27.620
All hail
Children of the Stars.
Yeah, but if the missile's real,
it won't matter if they jump.

27:27.620 --> 27:29.210
And if it's not?

27:29.210 --> 27:31.830
Aurora:
We wait for your arrival,
Noon Star Harvesters.

27:31.830 --> 27:34.710
All: All hail
Children of the Stars.

27:34.710 --> 27:36.380
Today the Saviors
will gather our souls.
Okay.

27:36.380 --> 27:38.330
I mean, but they're
true believers.

27:38.330 --> 27:40.880
How are we gonna get through
to them in nine minutes?

27:40.880 --> 27:42.620
I'm open to suggestions.

27:42.620 --> 27:45.210
All: All hail
Children of the Stars.

27:45.210 --> 27:46.380
[ Gunshot ]
Amari: Get out of here!

27:46.380 --> 27:47.920
Put -- Put it down!

27:47.920 --> 27:49.170
Get -- Get out! Get out!

27:49.170 --> 27:50.790
Put it down! Put it down!

27:50.790 --> 27:53.250
[ Gunshot ]

27:53.250 --> 27:56.080
Amari, it's Tim!
Amari: Bradford?!

27:56.080 --> 27:58.380
Yeah. You alright?

27:58.380 --> 28:00.580
Yeah, but Lewis took a bottle
to the head.

28:00.580 --> 28:02.290
Alright,
just put down the shotgun.

28:02.290 --> 28:04.330
They're robbing me.
I got to protect my store.

28:04.330 --> 28:06.420
We're here now,
so put it down.

28:06.420 --> 28:07.960
[ Glass crunching ]

28:07.960 --> 28:09.040
Put it on the counter.
Put it down.

28:09.040 --> 28:10.790
Okay.
O-Okay. Alright.

28:11.960 --> 28:13.620
Now we're coming in.

28:14.580 --> 28:15.710
Check him out.

28:17.460 --> 28:20.120
Hey. Let me see.
Ohh.

28:20.120 --> 28:21.330
Okay, you're gonna need
stitches,

28:21.330 --> 28:22.790
but it's nothing
life-threatening.

28:22.790 --> 28:24.120
Keep pressure on it.

28:24.120 --> 28:25.500
Why don't you take him around
the corner to your house?

28:25.500 --> 28:27.210
No, I-I-I can't leave
my store.

28:27.210 --> 28:29.080
It's just stuff, Amari.
The missile is coming, alright?

28:29.080 --> 28:30.460
You should be
with your family.

28:30.460 --> 28:32.380
Yeah, but if it's not,
I'll lose everything.

28:32.380 --> 28:33.670
[ Scoffs ]
No wonder you need counseling.

28:33.670 --> 28:35.080
What the hell is that
supposed to mean?

28:35.080 --> 28:36.580
It means that nothing
is more important

28:36.580 --> 28:38.460
than the people you love,
and they need you right now.

28:40.330 --> 28:41.920
We'll take care of
your shop.

28:41.920 --> 28:43.330
[ Sirens wailing,
horns honking ]

28:43.330 --> 28:45.000
O-Okay.

28:45.000 --> 28:46.580
Alright, come on.
Let's get him up.
Okay.

28:46.580 --> 28:49.460
You're right.
You're right.
[ Groans ]

28:49.460 --> 28:51.380
Thank you.
Let's go. Come on.

28:56.120 --> 28:58.170
Busted.

28:58.170 --> 28:59.960
How much time
we got left?

29:03.120 --> 29:04.420
Enough.

29:04.420 --> 29:05.210
[ Cork squeaks ]

29:06.710 --> 29:08.960
[ Scoffs ]

29:08.960 --> 29:12.380
Uh, I'm not
a whiskey girl.

29:12.380 --> 29:14.170
[ Sirens wail in distance ]

29:17.920 --> 29:19.880
To the end of the world.

29:19.880 --> 29:21.670
Whenever that may be.

29:21.670 --> 29:23.040
[ Bottles clink ]

29:24.750 --> 29:27.620
This shelter
was built in the '50s.

29:27.620 --> 29:30.670
Now, nukes are 10 times
as powerful today.

29:30.670 --> 29:33.960
Odds are good that this building
collapses when the blast hits.

29:33.960 --> 29:34.960
Shut up, Oscar.

29:34.960 --> 29:36.790
It's basic science, my man.

29:36.790 --> 29:38.330
Try not to sound
so happy about it.

29:38.330 --> 29:39.500
What can I say?
I'm a happy guy.

29:39.500 --> 29:41.790
Not like mami over here.

29:41.790 --> 29:43.580
[ Chuckles ]
So sad.

29:43.580 --> 29:45.380
Don't you laugh
at our grief.

29:45.380 --> 29:47.620
He's trying to provoke you.
Don't let him.

29:47.620 --> 29:49.750
Oscar: You got me
all wrong, Counselor.

29:49.750 --> 29:53.000
What we have here is
a cathartic opportunity.

29:53.000 --> 29:57.040
Two paths --
forgiveness or revenge.

29:57.040 --> 29:59.250
Oh, three, three paths.

29:59.250 --> 30:02.040
I forgot.
I forgot about the missile.
[ Chuckles ]

30:02.040 --> 30:04.170
Oh, I ain't looking
for forgiveness.

30:04.170 --> 30:05.830
And little papi over there

30:05.830 --> 30:08.210
can try for revenge
if he likes.

30:08.210 --> 30:10.120
But he'll just end up
in the ground like his kid.

30:10.120 --> 30:10.960
You --

30:10.960 --> 30:12.290
Come here!

30:12.290 --> 30:13.670
[ Indistinct shouting ]

30:13.670 --> 30:14.790
How dare you!

30:14.790 --> 30:15.790
Sit down. Shut up.

30:15.790 --> 30:17.960
Wesley: Sit down now.
Sit down.

30:17.960 --> 30:19.420
It's okay.
He's not worth it.

30:19.420 --> 30:20.790
Nolan: One more word
out of any of them,

30:20.790 --> 30:21.830
we're gagging them all.
Happy to.

30:21.830 --> 30:23.620
One more word.

30:26.210 --> 30:28.040
You okay?

30:28.040 --> 30:30.210
No.

30:30.210 --> 30:35.290
♪♪

30:39.540 --> 30:43.170
Aurora: Today the Saviors
will gather our souls.

30:43.170 --> 30:45.460
All: All hail
Children of the Stars.

30:45.460 --> 30:47.710
Aurora: The worthy will ascend
into the heavens.

30:47.710 --> 30:48.790
All: All hail
Children of the Stars.
Excuse me.

30:48.790 --> 30:50.040
I hate to interrupt.

30:50.040 --> 30:51.620
I just have a question.

30:51.620 --> 30:53.460
The time
for questions is done.

30:53.460 --> 30:55.670
Totally. I just --

30:56.960 --> 30:58.670
Whoa. Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!
Wait. Wait. Wait. Wait. Hold on.

30:58.670 --> 31:00.120
Hold on.
Who's Jedediah?

31:00.120 --> 31:01.380
You mentioned him earlier.

31:01.380 --> 31:02.540
He is the prophet

31:02.540 --> 31:05.170
who helped us cast away
our earthly possessions

31:05.170 --> 31:06.120
and see the truth.

31:09.880 --> 31:11.210
About the aliens?

31:11.210 --> 31:12.830
They're not aliens.

31:12.830 --> 31:15.250
They're spirits
from another universe.

31:15.250 --> 31:17.750
And where is he?
Jedediah.

31:17.750 --> 31:19.380
He's joining us
in the heavens.

31:19.380 --> 31:20.620
Does that mean
he's on another rooftop?

31:20.620 --> 31:22.170
No.
This is the one true spot,

31:22.170 --> 31:23.750
where -- where the chosen
will ascend.

31:23.750 --> 31:25.580
And yet he's not here.

31:25.580 --> 31:27.120
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

31:27.120 --> 31:29.250
What's your name?

31:30.330 --> 31:31.500
Aurora.

31:31.500 --> 31:32.830
How old are you, Aurora?

31:32.830 --> 31:36.040
19.

31:36.040 --> 31:37.290
It is
the age of the chosen.

31:37.290 --> 31:39.290
Aren't you scared?

31:39.290 --> 31:40.670
[ Voice breaking ]
No, I'm at peace.
It's just...

31:43.540 --> 31:45.170
...I don't like heights.

31:45.170 --> 31:47.290
I don't blame you.
It's a long way down.

31:47.290 --> 31:50.120
So why do you have to step
off the roof to ascend?

31:52.250 --> 31:54.250
'Cause that's the way
it must be.
Why?

31:54.250 --> 31:56.540
The spirits love you.
Oh, yes.

31:56.540 --> 31:58.290
And they're traveling
all this way to save you.

31:58.290 --> 32:00.080
Do you think they really care
how you meet them,

32:00.080 --> 32:02.540
as long as you do it
with open arms?

32:02.540 --> 32:06.420
♪♪

32:06.420 --> 32:08.500
It is a test to our faith.

32:08.500 --> 32:10.880
There is no doubt
you have faith, all of you.

32:10.880 --> 32:13.000
So come down now,

32:13.000 --> 32:15.620
and we'll wait for them together
on solid ground.

32:15.620 --> 32:20.040
♪♪

32:20.040 --> 32:21.380
I promise it'll be okay.

32:21.380 --> 32:27.040
♪♪

32:27.040 --> 32:32.750
♪♪

32:34.790 --> 32:36.580
[ Radio crackles ]
Sgt. Grey:
Attention, all units.

32:36.580 --> 32:38.960
Missile alert is a false alarm.

32:38.960 --> 32:40.210
I repeat -- the alert
is a false alarm.
Oh, thank God.

32:40.210 --> 32:41.710
What does --
What does that mean?

32:41.710 --> 32:42.790
It means
they're not coming.

32:44.920 --> 32:49.040
[ Telephone ringing ]

32:49.040 --> 32:51.380
The danger's over.
Okay?

32:51.380 --> 32:52.790
Okay.

32:52.790 --> 32:54.170
Does that mean
Daddy'll be here soon?

32:57.000 --> 32:59.330
Yeah. Yeah.
Woman: I know, right?

32:59.330 --> 33:01.580
-Crazy today.
-This was unbelievable.

33:01.580 --> 33:02.830
Oh, you know what?

33:02.830 --> 33:05.080
Honey,
I will be right back.

33:05.080 --> 33:07.120
Hey. Hi.

33:07.120 --> 33:10.040
Um [Chuckles] thanks
for watching my kid.

33:10.040 --> 33:11.120
Oh, my pleasure.

33:11.120 --> 33:12.290
She's super cute.

33:12.290 --> 33:13.210
Thanks.

33:13.210 --> 33:14.620
Uh, hey, listen.

33:14.620 --> 33:16.960
You work for Social Services,
right?

33:16.960 --> 33:18.250
I do.

33:18.250 --> 33:20.290
Can I ask you
a theoretical question?

33:20.290 --> 33:21.880
Sure.

33:21.880 --> 33:24.580
Okay, say, uh,
there's a divorced couple

33:24.580 --> 33:26.580
and, uh, the dad
has sole custody

33:26.580 --> 33:28.880
and the mom
has supervised visitations

33:28.880 --> 33:31.500
and an emergency comes up

33:31.500 --> 33:34.210
and she can't
get in touch with him --

33:34.210 --> 33:37.460
So she picks her super cute
daughter up from school

33:37.460 --> 33:38.620
to keep her safe.

33:38.620 --> 33:40.170
Yeah.

33:40.170 --> 33:41.790
Is that bad?

33:43.540 --> 33:45.960
To the court,
it's not good.

33:45.960 --> 33:49.620
You know that technically
it's a parental abduction.

33:49.620 --> 33:51.670
Yeah, but even given
the circumstances?

33:51.670 --> 33:54.540
I'm not saying a judge wouldn't
take it into consideration,

33:54.540 --> 33:57.710
but if the factors that led
to the visitation restrictions

33:57.710 --> 33:58.880
are serious enough,

33:58.880 --> 34:00.670
it won't matter.

34:00.670 --> 34:04.540
You could lose
all access to her.

34:04.540 --> 34:06.710
Sgt. Grey: Harper,
have you heard from Nolan?

34:06.710 --> 34:08.290
He's the only cop
that hasn't checked in.

34:08.290 --> 34:09.790
What?

34:09.790 --> 34:11.250
Officer Nolan.
Your rookie?

34:11.250 --> 34:12.330
Have you heard from him?

34:14.420 --> 34:17.250
No, sir, I-I haven't talked
to him since this morning.

34:17.250 --> 34:25.500
♪♪

34:25.500 --> 34:26.790
One minute.

34:28.920 --> 34:30.960
Will we know
when it hits?

34:30.960 --> 34:34.170
Yeah. We'll feel the shock wave
and likely some heat.

34:34.170 --> 34:35.330
Hopefully
not too much heat.

34:35.330 --> 34:37.080
[ Handcuff clicks ]

34:37.080 --> 34:38.960
[ Metal clicking ]

34:38.960 --> 34:43.670
♪♪

34:43.670 --> 34:45.540
30 seconds.

34:45.540 --> 34:50.880
♪♪

34:50.880 --> 34:52.380
[ Handcuffs click ]

34:52.380 --> 34:57.460
♪♪

34:57.460 --> 34:59.290
♪♪

34:59.290 --> 35:01.790
[ People shouting ]

35:04.380 --> 35:05.670
[ Shouting continues ]

35:05.670 --> 35:08.920
[ Gunshots ]

35:08.920 --> 35:09.960
[ Gasps ]

35:11.670 --> 35:13.500
[ Whimpers ]

35:13.500 --> 35:14.880
[ Bullet ricochets,
people scream ]

35:14.880 --> 35:16.830
[ Gunshot ]

35:16.830 --> 35:18.540
[ Woman breathing heavily ]

35:18.540 --> 35:19.830
[ Gunshot ]

35:19.830 --> 35:22.120
[ People screaming ]

35:22.120 --> 35:24.920
Ohh!
[ Groaning ]

35:24.920 --> 35:26.880
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

35:26.880 --> 35:27.710
Prisoner secured!

35:27.710 --> 35:29.170
Nolan.

35:31.670 --> 35:33.750
Everybody, be calm.

35:33.750 --> 35:35.880
♪♪

35:35.880 --> 35:38.120
Thanks for the diversion,
buddy.
[ Groaning ]

35:38.120 --> 35:39.880
Let the judge go.
Sure I will,

35:39.880 --> 35:41.500
just as soon as
I'm outside.

35:41.500 --> 35:43.000
What about the missile?
Well, if it's real,

35:43.000 --> 35:44.420
I'm not gonna
feel it anyways.

35:44.420 --> 35:46.040
I'm just gonna wink
right out of existence.

35:46.040 --> 35:48.000
I don't want to spend the rest
of my days in solitary.

35:48.000 --> 35:50.670
If you even twitch,
I'm gonna cut your carotid.

35:50.670 --> 35:54.920
♪♪

35:54.920 --> 35:56.790
No! Don't open it!

35:56.790 --> 35:59.380
[ Door squeaks ]

35:59.380 --> 36:01.420
[ People shouting ]

36:04.460 --> 36:06.080
Hey.

36:06.080 --> 36:07.710
Ugh!

36:07.710 --> 36:09.920
[ People shout ]

36:09.920 --> 36:11.920
Looks like you'll be spending
some time in solitary after all.

36:11.920 --> 36:13.120
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

36:13.120 --> 36:15.540
So, no missile?
False alarm.

36:15.540 --> 36:17.670
Heat wave caused a malfunction
at Edwards Air Force Base.

36:17.670 --> 36:21.880
♪♪

36:21.880 --> 36:23.500
Where's Wesley?

36:23.500 --> 36:25.540
I don't know.
He was just here.

36:25.540 --> 36:32.120
♪♪

36:32.120 --> 36:38.670
♪♪

36:38.670 --> 36:40.330
Wesley.

36:42.540 --> 36:44.040
Oh, my God.

36:44.040 --> 36:45.540
Get an ambulance!

36:45.540 --> 36:47.540
Oh, my God.
It's okay, baby.

36:47.540 --> 36:49.710
I'm here. I'm here. I'm here.
Stay with me. Stay with me.

36:54.120 --> 36:56.580
35-year-old male
in hypovolemic shock,

36:56.580 --> 36:58.960
stab wound to the left chest,
possible pneumothorax.

36:58.960 --> 37:02.830
Doctor: Alert the O.R.
This guy's jumping the line.

37:02.830 --> 37:04.750
Nurse Lisa:
We've got him from here.
Is he gonna be okay?

37:04.750 --> 37:06.540
It depends on the extent
of the internal damage,

37:06.540 --> 37:07.880
but we're gonna do
everything we can.

37:07.880 --> 37:09.000
Sorry. I've gotta go.

37:09.000 --> 37:11.460
[ P.A. system chatter ]

37:11.460 --> 37:15.210
♪♪

37:15.210 --> 37:16.960
[ Door buzzes ]

37:16.960 --> 37:19.000
You can't really
blame a guy for trying.

37:19.000 --> 37:20.210
To commit a felony?

37:20.210 --> 37:22.170
It's literally what I do
for a living.

37:22.170 --> 37:24.290
Was it all
just a game to you?

37:24.290 --> 37:26.420
Did you feel any fear
at all?

37:26.420 --> 37:27.620
Honestly? No.

37:27.620 --> 37:28.750
[ Handcuffs click ]

37:28.750 --> 37:30.210
Guys like me
are wired differently.

37:30.210 --> 37:33.460
I don't really do fear
or anxiety.

37:33.460 --> 37:35.540
On the flip side,
I have really poor
impulse control.

37:35.540 --> 37:37.540
He, you think
I could get a soda?

37:37.540 --> 37:39.330
No.
Donovan:
Is my daughter here?

37:39.330 --> 37:43.210
Where's my daughter?
Where is she? Lila!

37:43.210 --> 37:45.120
What's going on?
My daughter -- Lila.

37:45.120 --> 37:46.080
Please tell me
she's here.

37:46.080 --> 37:47.210
Daddy!

37:47.210 --> 37:48.500
Oh, God.

37:48.500 --> 37:50.330
[ Sighs ]

37:50.330 --> 37:52.580
Are you okay, baby?
Yeah.

37:52.580 --> 37:54.330
Mommy picked me up at school
'cause of the missile,

37:54.330 --> 37:55.790
but it's not real.

37:55.790 --> 37:57.120
I-I was trying to get
in touch with you --

37:57.120 --> 37:58.250
You had no right!

37:58.250 --> 38:00.210
I showed up,
and she was gone.

38:00.210 --> 38:02.540
The school was closed.
I had no idea where she was!

38:02.540 --> 38:04.500
Sir, I understand your fear,
but your child was safe here.

38:04.500 --> 38:05.920
Donovan:
Y-You don't understand.

38:05.920 --> 38:08.500
She has no custody rights.
She kidnapped my kid.

38:08.500 --> 38:10.420
I did not --
No, no, no, no.
I want her arrested.

38:11.830 --> 38:14.040
Daddy, no.

38:14.040 --> 38:16.920
Sir, with all due respect,
I think you're overreacting.

38:16.920 --> 38:19.210
I'm what?
When you consider
everything that happened --

38:19.210 --> 38:21.000
I-I don't care.
This is the last straw.

38:21.000 --> 38:22.830
She said things had changed,
that she had changed,

38:22.830 --> 38:24.670
but it was just another lie.
No, it wasn't.

38:26.120 --> 38:27.460
How the hell
would you know?

38:27.460 --> 38:29.620
Because she's here,

38:29.620 --> 38:32.000
back in uniform,
training me.

38:32.000 --> 38:34.420
I couldn't figure out why
until just this moment.

38:34.420 --> 38:36.170
I mean,
she had a golden ticket.

38:36.170 --> 38:37.790
She could have gone anywhere
in the department,

38:37.790 --> 38:39.290
anywhere she wanted.

38:39.290 --> 38:41.040
So, why the hell
would she get back in blues

38:41.040 --> 38:42.710
and spend her days
training a guy like me?

38:42.710 --> 38:46.670
I knew whatever the reason was,
it had to be primal,

38:46.670 --> 38:50.250
powerful enough to...overcome
her inherent arrogance.

38:52.330 --> 38:56.290
And now I see your daughter,
and I see exactly why

38:56.290 --> 38:58.460
she's willing to sacrifice
what she does best

38:58.460 --> 39:00.830
for the person
she loves the most.

39:00.830 --> 39:02.790
Lila: Please, Daddy.

39:02.790 --> 39:04.960
I made her promise --
no more lying.

39:04.960 --> 39:07.040
[ Sighs ]

39:07.040 --> 39:09.120
It's true.

39:12.670 --> 39:14.250
I'm trying here, Don.

39:14.250 --> 39:16.960
I have been lost,

39:16.960 --> 39:20.380
and I am trying
to find my way back.

39:20.380 --> 39:21.710
And I am gonna make
mistakes.

39:21.710 --> 39:23.000
[ Sniffles ]

39:23.000 --> 39:24.960
And I'm gonna
fall on my face a lot.

39:24.960 --> 39:26.580
But when that alert
came in,

39:26.580 --> 39:28.580
the only thing
I could think about

39:28.580 --> 39:30.580
was making sure
that she was safe.

39:30.580 --> 39:33.080
That is the only thing
that matters to me now.

39:42.080 --> 39:43.880
Okay.

39:43.880 --> 39:46.620
Okay.

39:46.620 --> 39:48.120
Let's go home.

39:53.880 --> 39:58.120
Go hug your mama.

39:58.120 --> 39:59.960
[ Butch Walker's "When Canyons
Ruled The City" plays ]

39:59.960 --> 40:01.710
[ Sighs deeply ]

40:01.710 --> 40:06.000
♪♪

40:06.000 --> 40:09.620
[ Sniffles ]

40:09.620 --> 40:12.750
I love you, cutie. Okay?

40:12.750 --> 40:16.710
♪ Laurel was a girl I knew,
made of dirt and stone ♪

40:16.710 --> 40:18.080
♪ Pretty, hip
in younger years ♪
[ Clears throat ]

40:18.080 --> 40:19.960
♪ But now she sits alone ♪

40:19.960 --> 40:22.880
♪ With a hundred thousand
architectural disasters ♪

40:22.880 --> 40:25.540
♪ That she calls home ♪
Thanks.

40:25.540 --> 40:27.750
Seems like a great kid.

40:27.750 --> 40:30.710
Yeah. She is.

40:30.710 --> 40:32.710
♪ She tried to get the credit ♪

40:32.710 --> 40:34.460
♪ Sometimes more
than she deserved ♪

40:34.460 --> 40:36.750
♪ Like those cheesy
'80s movies ♪

40:36.750 --> 40:38.670
♪ Epitomizing all things
we'd come to know ♪

40:38.670 --> 40:41.000
Hey. Sure I can't
get you something?

40:41.000 --> 40:42.540
I'm fine.

40:42.540 --> 40:45.330
What's taking so long?

40:45.330 --> 40:47.170
So, do you want me
to talk to my buddy

40:47.170 --> 40:48.580
about the cockroaches?
[ Chuckles ]

40:48.580 --> 40:50.750
No, thanks.

40:50.750 --> 40:53.210
After today, I've decided that
I'm okay with the wedding.

40:53.210 --> 40:55.210
I know they seem
really happy.

40:55.210 --> 40:56.830
And truth be told,
I was only with him

40:56.830 --> 40:58.460
because I couldn't afford
to move out.

40:58.460 --> 41:00.330
And she knew that, so...

41:00.330 --> 41:02.380
Does that mean
we're going to the wedding?

41:02.380 --> 41:06.000
No, but I might
get them a present.

41:06.000 --> 41:08.170
With a roach in it?
Maybe. [ Chuckles ]

41:08.170 --> 41:10.830
You are a bad influence.

41:10.830 --> 41:12.830
Love you, too. Bye.

41:12.830 --> 41:15.460
So, Henry says hello

41:15.460 --> 41:18.420
and that I should move
the hell out of Los Angeles.
[ Chuckles ]

41:18.420 --> 41:20.170
That's a smart kid.
What'd you tell him?

41:20.170 --> 41:21.830
That there was never
any real danger

41:21.830 --> 41:23.080
because you had my back.

41:23.080 --> 41:24.420
And your front.

41:24.420 --> 41:26.080
[ Elevator bell dings ]

41:27.880 --> 41:29.710
Hey.
Harper: Hey.

41:29.710 --> 41:31.040
I hope it's okay
that I'm here.

41:31.040 --> 41:32.670
[ Clears throat ]
Yeah.

41:32.670 --> 41:33.920
How's Wesley?

41:33.920 --> 41:35.620
We're waiting to find out.
Join us.

41:35.620 --> 41:40.750
♪♪

41:40.750 --> 41:42.380
Is he okay?

41:42.380 --> 41:43.420
The surgery went well.

41:43.420 --> 41:45.000
The doctor repaired
his lung.

41:45.000 --> 41:47.040
As long as there are
no complications,

41:47.040 --> 41:49.750
he should make
a full recovery.
Thank you.

41:49.750 --> 41:51.540
They'll move him into ICU
in a few hours.

41:51.540 --> 41:53.170
I'll come get you
so you can see him.

41:53.170 --> 41:56.250
♪♪

41:56.250 --> 41:57.790
He's gonna be okay.
[ Chuckles ]

41:57.790 --> 42:01.620
♪♪

42:01.620 --> 42:02.920
[ Laughs ]

42:02.920 --> 42:06.710
♪♪

42:06.710 --> 42:07.750
[ Sighs ]

42:07.750 --> 42:09.080
[ Laughs ]

42:09.080 --> 42:12.540
♪♪

